  <p>
   The sign for "hammer" is done by miming the use of a 
			hammer.  Grab an imaginary hammer using an "S"-handshape and 
			make two quick strikes on an imaginary nail.  (If you hit your 
			thumb make sure to let loose with an imaginary yell. ;-)
   <br/>
  </p>
  <p>
   HAMMER:
   <br/>
   <img border="0" height="236" src="/images/hammer5.jpg" width="245"/>
   <img border="0" height="236" src="/images/hammer6.jpg" width="245"/>
   <img border="0" height="236" src="/images/hammer5.jpg" width="245"/>
   <img border="0" height="236" src="/images/hammer6.jpg" width="245"/>
   <br/>
  </p>
  <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
  <br/>
  "Hammer a nail"
  <br/>
  Hold a "pretend' nail in your left hand and hit it twice with your "pretend" 
  hammer.
  <p>
   <img border="0" height="236" src="/images/hammer7.jpg" width="245"/>
   <img border="0" height="236" src="/images/hammer8.jpg" width="245"/>
   <img border="0" height="236" src="/images/hammer7.jpg" width="245"/>
   <img border="0" height="236" src="/images/hammer8.jpg" width="245"/>
   <br/>
  </p>
  <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
  <p>
   Note:
   <br/>
   Yes, as a matter of fact, I
   <i>
    can
   </i>
   amuse myself for
   <i>
    hours
   </i>
   .
  </p>
